                     <interp inst="def1-2781-18411025" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES ANDREWS</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18411025-2781-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18411025-2781-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18411025-2781-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18411025-cd-199" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18411025-2781-offence-1 t18411025-cd-199"></join>24th of September</rs>, 1lb. 10oz. of leather, value 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18411025-name-1276" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1276" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1276" type="surname" value="BUCK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1276" type="given" value="JOHN HACK"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18411025-2781-offence-1 t18411025-name-1276"></join>John Hack Buck</persName>, and others, his masters.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411025-name-1277" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1277" type="surname" value="WRIGHT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1277" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL WRIGHT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable P</hi> 172.) I received information, and watched at Willow-walk, Grange-road, Bermondsey, and at half-past seven o'clock in the evening of the 24th of September I saw the prisoner come out of the prosecutor's premises—I stopped him about forty yards off, and said I wanted to speak to him—he said, "What for?—I said I was an officer, and I must take him on suspicion of robbing his employers—he said, "Oh, my God, what shall I do?"—I took him in their count<lb></lb>ing-house, and found three pieces of leather wrapped round the calves of his legs, one piece in his hat, and another piece in his pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411025-name-1278" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1278" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1278" type="surname" value="STOKES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1278" type="given" value="JAMES HENRY"></interp>JAMES HENRY STOKES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am foreman to Messrs. John Hack Buck, and four others. The prisoner had been in their employ three or four years—I watched him on the evening stated, and saw him put two pieces of leather in his boots—I believe the whole of this leather is my master's—the prisoner was not justified in taking it off the premises.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184110250178"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did he take work home to do? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—I believe he has four children dependent on him.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
